PAT_ENC.name: PAT_ENC
PAT_ENC.description:
The patient encounter table contains one record for each patient encounter in your system. By default, this table does not contain Registration or PCP/Clinic Change contacts (encounter types 1 and 31). It does contain all appointments, office visits, telephone encounters, and other types of encounters. The primary key for the patient encounter table is PAT_ENC_CSN_ID.


Note that there is an index named EIX_FILT_PAT_ENC_RFL on the REFERRAL_ID column in Oracle that does not appear in the index list. The index is created by EFN_FAUX_RFL_FILT_INX.

columns.name: PAT_ID
columns.description: The unique ID assigned to the patient record. This ID may be encrypted if you have elected to use enterprise reporting�s encryption utility.

columns.name: PAT_ENC_DATE_REAL
columns.description: A unique contact date in decimal format. The integer portion of the number indicates the date of contact. The digits after the decimal distinguish different contacts on the same date and are unique for each contact on that date. For example, .00 is the first/only contact, .01 is the second contact, etc.

columns.name: PAT_ENC_CSN_ID
columns.description: A unique serial number for this encounter. This number is unique across all patients and encounters in the system.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE
columns.description: The date of this contact in calendar format.

columns.name: PCP_PROV_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the provider record for the patient�s General Primary Care Provider as of the date of the encounter. This ID may be encrypted if you have elected to use enterprise reporting�s security utility.

columns.name: VISIT_PROV_ID
columns.description: The unique ID for the visit provider associated with this encounter. In cases where there are multiple providers for one encounter, this is the ID of the first provider in the list. This item may be NULL if there is no provider for this encounter. This ID may be encrypted.

columns.name: VISIT_PROV_TITLE_NAME
columns.description: The visit provider�s provider title (SER 5). See VISIT_PROV_ID above for the definition of visit provider.

columns.name: DEPARTMENT_ID
columns.description: The ID of the department for the encounter. If there are multiple departments for the encounter, this is the ID of the first department in the list.

columns.name: ENC_CLOSED_YN
columns.description: A flag that signifies if this encounter is closed as of the time of the enterprise reporting extract. This column will have the value Y, N or null. Null indicates that closing the encounter does not apply, such as a future appointment.

columns.name: ENC_CLOSED_USER_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the system user who closed the patient encounter. This ID may be encrypted.

columns.name: ENC_CLOSED_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: ENC_CLOSE_DATE
columns.description: The date on which the patient encounter was closed.

columns.name: APPT_STATUS_C_NAME
columns.description: The category value associated with the appointment status of the encounter as of the most recent enterprise reporting extract, such as 1 � Scheduled, 2 � Completed, 3 � Canceled, etc.

columns.name: APPT_CANC_USER_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the user who canceled the appointment.

columns.name: APPT_CANC_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: CHECKIN_USER_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the system user who checked in the patient for this encounter. If the encounter has not been through the Check In process this field will be NULL. This ID may be encrypted.

columns.name: CHECKIN_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: HOSP_ADMSN_TIME
columns.description: The date and time that the patient was first admitted to the facility, bedded in the ED, or confirmed for an HOV for this contact, regardless of patient's base patient class.

columns.name: HOSP_DISCHRG_TIME
columns.description: The hospital discharge date and time for this patient contact.

columns.name: HOSP_ADMSN_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The category value for the type of admission for this encounter.

columns.name: NONCVRED_SERVICE_YN
columns.description: A flag used to indicate whether the appointment is scheduled in a service not covered by the patient's coverage benefits. The flag is set to "Y" when the service is not covered and an "N" when it is covered.

columns.name: REFERRAL_REQ_YN
columns.description: A flag used to indicate whether an appointment requires a referral as determined by the visit coverage. This flag is set to �Y� when the appointment requires a referral. If the appointment does not require a referral, it is set to �N."

columns.name: REFERRAL_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the referral record linked to this appointment.

columns.name: ACCOUNT_ID
columns.description: The ID number of the guarantor account assigned to the visit at the time it is scheduled or when it is checked in. This ID may be encrypted.

columns.name: COVERAGE_ID
columns.description: The ID number of the coverage record assigned to the visit at the time it is scheduled or when it is checked in. This ID may be encrypted.

columns.name: PRIMARY_LOC_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the patient�s primary location as of the contact date of the encounter. Note: This may not be the same as the patient�s current primary location.

columns.name: CHARGE_SLIP_NUMBER
columns.description: The encounter form number or charge slip number assigned to this encounter. Note: The charge slip number is also stored in the financial table CLARITY_TDL. You can use this field to link to CLARITY_TDL to identify financial transactions associated with the encounter.

columns.name: COPAY_DUE
columns.description: The dollar amount shown in the Copay Due field of the scheduling system's Check In Patient activity. This amount may be calculated by the system using the patient's coverage benefit information or be manually entered by a user. This field may also be empty if no copay amount was entered when the patient's appointment was checked in.

columns.name: UPDATE_DATE
columns.description: The time this patient encounter was pulled into enterprise reporting.

columns.name: HSP_ACCOUNT_ID
columns.description: The ID number of the hospital billing account assigned to the encounter.

columns.name: INPATIENT_DATA_ID
columns.description: The ID number of the record used to determine how inpatient data is stored for the encounter.

columns.name: IP_EPISODE_ID
columns.description: The ID number of the inpatient episode of care. This includes discharges from the ED.

columns.name: CONTACT_COMMENT
columns.description: Comments entered by the provider for the contact.

columns.name: OUTGOING_CALL_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether a call associated with a telephone encounter was initiated by the patient or by the clinic / hospital. A "Y" indicates an outgoing call placed by the clinic / hospital while an "N" indicates and incoming call from the patient.

columns.name: REFERRAL_SOURCE_ID
columns.description: The referral ID number of the referring physician. This physician may be from an external organization.

columns.name: REFERRAL_SOURCE_ID_REFERRING_PROV_NAM
columns.description: The name of the referral source.

columns.name: BMI
columns.description: This is the patient's Body Mass Index, which is calculated based on the recorded height and weight.

columns.name: BSA
columns.description: This is the patient's Body Surface Area, which is calculated based on the recorded height and weight.

columns.name: AVS_PRINT_TM
columns.description: The instant that the After Visit Summary (AVS) was printed for this encounter.

columns.name: AVS_FIRST_USER_ID
columns.description: Unique ID of the user who first prints out the After Visit Summary (AVS) for the encounter.

columns.name: AVS_FIRST_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: ENC_MED_FRZ_RSN_C_NAME
columns.description: The encounter medication freeze reason's category value.

columns.name: EFFECTIVE_DATE_DT
columns.description: The date of the encounter. The returned date is handled differently depending on the contact type of the encounter: If it is a surgery encounter, the date of the surgery will be returned. If it is a Hospital encounter, Admission/Discharge/Transfer (ADT) info will be used to return an appropriate date. If ADT info cannot be found, then the  Hospital Admission date (I EPT 18850) will be returned. If the Hospital Admission Date cannot be found, the temporary admission date (I EPT 18846) will be returned..

columns.name: DISCHARGE_DATE_DT
columns.description: The discharge date for the encounter.

columns.name: BEN_ENG_SP_AMT
columns.description: Stores the adjudicated self-pay amount (the amount required to be paid by the patient) when determining the copay amount for the visit.

columns.name: BEN_ADJ_COPAY_AMT
columns.description: Stores the adjudicated copy amount for the visit according to the patient's coverage benefits.

columns.name: BEN_ADJ_METHOD_C_NAME
columns.description: Flag to indicate if and how the adjudicated copay was overridden
entries: Service Area Level Override Programming Point

columns.name: ENC_CREATE_USER_ID
columns.description: The ID number of the user who create the patient or encounter record.

columns.name: ENC_CREATE_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: ENC_INSTANT
columns.description: The instant an encounter was created

columns.name: EFFECTIVE_DATE_DTTM
columns.description: The start date and time of an encounter. The start date is pulled from the date stored in the EFFECTIVE_DATE_DT column. The time references the first populated time in the following fields: hospital admission time (EPT 18851), hospital temporary admission time (EPT 18847), ADT arrival time (EPT 10815), and expected admission time (EPT 10300).  The SlicerDicer reporting application uses this column to determine the EffectiveStartDate of encounters.

columns.name: CALCULATED_ENC_STAT_C_NAME
columns.description: A status flag used to  determine whether to include data from the encounter in the SlicerDicer reporting application. Statuses includes 1-Possible (e.g., the encounter is a scheduled outpatient appointment or the admission is pending) or 2-Complete (e.g., the appointment is complete, the admission is discharged).

columns.name: CAN_LET_C_NAME
columns.description: This column links to the type of canceled appointment letter sent for this patient encounter. Some examples are "No Letter", "No Show","Cancelation Letter", etc. This category column is linked to ZC_LET.LET_C.

columns.name: SUP_PROV_C_NAME
columns.description: This column links to information about the Type of Supervising provider.

columns.name: SUP_PROV_REV_TM
columns.description: This column contains the date and time when the supervising provider submitted his or her review

columns.name: MEDS_REQUEST_PHR_ID
columns.description: The pharmacy identifier from which the medications were requested.

columns.name: MEDS_REQUEST_PHR_ID_PHARMACY_NAME
columns.description: The name of the pharmacy.

columns.name: PHYS_BP
columns.description: This contains the patient's blood pressure that was entered during the patient encounter.

columns.name: VITALS_TAKEN_TM
columns.description: Holds the time the vitals were taken

columns.name: DOC_HX_SOURCE_C_NAME
columns.description: Stores the source of entry for the history documentation.  This category column is linked to ZC_HISTORY_SOURCE.HISTORY_SOURCE_C.

columns.name: APPT_LET_C_NAME
columns.description: This column links to the type of appointment letter that was sent to this patient for this patient encounter. Some examples are "No Letter", "Appt Letter", etc.  This category column is linked to ZC_LET.LET_C.

columns.name: APPTMT_LET_INST
columns.description: If an appointment letter has been printed for this patient encounter, this column will list the date and time it was printed. If multiple letters were printed, we'll list the date and time of the most recent one.

columns.name: ADT_PAT_CLASS_C_NAME
columns.description: The category value corresponding to the Admission/Discharge/Transfer (ADT) patient classification for this patient contact.

columns.name: OTHER_BLOCK_ID
columns.description: Stores "Other" Summary Blocks (non-IP, ED, OpTime)

columns.name: OTHER_BLOCK_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: Indicates the specific type of the episode summary, whose ID is stored in I EPT 1970.

columns.name: HSP_ACCT_ADV_DTTM
columns.description: If the Hospital Account Advisor is turned on, this item records the date and time that the advisor's recommendation was accepted or rejected.

columns.name: TEL_ENC_MSG_RGRDING
columns.description: Free-text field containing user entered information regarding a telephone encounter message.

columns.name: MSG_PRIORITY_C_NAME
columns.description: Indicates the priority of the routed message.

columns.name: MSG_CALLER_NAME
columns.description: The name of the caller who left this message

columns.name: AVS_LAST_PRINT_DTTM
columns.description: Records the instant the After Visit Summary was last printed

columns.name: MED_LIST_UPDATE_DTTM
columns.description: If a patient's prescriptions or Facility-Administered Medications (FAMs) are updated (signed, modified, or discontinued; or other med reconciliation actions are changed) after the After Visit Summary (AVS) has been printed, this item is updated to hold a timestamp indicating the last time that such updates were made. It is left blank if no AVS has been printed yet.

columns.name: PAT_ENC_CSN
columns.description: The unique contact serial number for this contact. This number is unique across all patient encounters in your system. If you use IntraConnect, this is the Unique Contact Identifier (UCI).

columns.name: CHKOUT_USER_ID
columns.description: The unique ID number of the user who completed the check out process for the patient for this encounter. If the encounter has not been checked out, this field will appear as "null." This ID may be encrypted.

columns.name: CHKOUT_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: ENC_BILL_AREA_ID
columns.description: The bill area which should be assigned to charges created from this encounter. The available bill areas to choose from will be determined based on lists in the provider and department records.

columns.name: ENC_BILL_AREA_ID_BILL_AREA_NAME
columns.description: The record name of this bill area, financial subdivision, or financial division.

columns.name: DX_UNIQUE_COUNTER
columns.description: The number of unique diagnoses associated with this patient encounter. Unique diagnoses are stored in item EPT 18425, which is extracted by the DX_UNIQUE column in the PAT_ENC_DX table.

columns.name: COMMAUTO_SENDER_ID
columns.description: The unique user ID of the sender of the automatically generated communications.

columns.name: COMMAUTO_SENDER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: BENEFIT_ID
columns.description: The benefit record used to store discrete information about the patient's insurance benefits for this encounter.

columns.name: DO_NOT_BILL_INS_YN
columns.description: Indicates if a visit is marked as Do Not Bill Insurance.

columns.name: SELF_PAY_VISIT_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether a visit is self-pay.

columns.name: COPAY_OVERRIDDEN_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether the user has overridden the copay amount for this encounter.

columns.name: VISIT_NUMBER
columns.description: The visit number for the given contact.

columns.name: COPAY_RECEIPT_NUM
columns.description: The receipt number of the copay collected.

columns.name: BEN_ADJ_COINS_AMT
columns.description: The adjudicated coinsurance amount for the visit calculated by the benefits engine.

columns.name: TOBACCO_USE_VRFY_YN
columns.description: This column indicates whether the patient's tobacco usage has been verified. A Y indicates the usage was verified. An N or null indicates the tobacco usage was not verified. It extracts a virtual item, which is calculated using EPT-19202.

columns.name: ECHKIN_STATUS_C_NAME
columns.description: The status of the eCheck-In for this appointment.

columns.name: PB_VISIT_HAR_ID
columns.description: The hospital account record used by the Professional Billing system for a given contact.

columns.name: ATTR_DEPARTMENT_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the department that is associated with the encounter.

columns.name: ELIG_PLAN_SELECT_YN
columns.description: This item indicates if an eligibility plan is currently selected for this encounter.

columns.name: APPT_AUTH_STATUS_C_NAME
columns.description: The authorization status of an appointment based on the information stored in any authorization records linked to an appointment (EPT-23025).

columns.name: INTF_PRIMARY_PAT_ENC_CSN_ID
columns.description: Contains the CSN of the primary interface contact for this encounter.

columns.name: CONTACT_NUM
columns.description: The system-assigned number used to uniquely identify each of a given patient's encounters.

columns.name: RSN_FOR_NO_INC_MSG_C_NAME
columns.description: The reason for no inc. message Category ID for the patient encounter. Indicates the reason there is no incomplete message to send for the encounter.

columns.name: THREAD_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the thread for a telephone encounter that was sent to another user.

columns.name: PAT_ALG_RVW_INFO_C_NAME
columns.description: The patient's response to the "are these allergies correct?" question in Welcome.
entries: Don't know details of health issues
Exited before health issues were verified

columns.name: PAT_PROB_RVW_INFO_C_NAME
columns.description: The patient's response to the "are these problems correct?" question in Welcome.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_2
merged.description: This table supplements the PAT_ENC table. It contains additional information related to patient encounters or appointments.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_3
merged.description: This table supplements the PAT_ENC and PAT_ENC_2 tables. It contains additional information related to patient encounters or appointments.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_4
merged.description: This table supplements the PAT_ENC, PAT_ENC_2, and PAT_ENC_3 tables. It contains additional information related to patient encounters or appointments.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_5
merged.description: This table supplements the PAT_ENC, PAT_ENC_2, PAT_ENC_3, and PAT_ENC_4 tables. It contains additional information related to patient encounters or appointments.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_6
merged.description: This table supplements the PAT_ENC, PAT_ENC_2, PAT_ENC_3, PAT_ENC_4, and PAT_ENC_5  tables. It contains additional information related to patient encounters or appointments.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_7
merged.description: This table supplements the PAT_ENC, PAT_ENC_2, PAT_ENC_3, PAT_ENC_4, PAT_ENC_5, and PAT_ENC_6 tables. It contains additional information related to patient encounters or appointments.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_PAS
merged.description: PAS items for a patient encounter.

merged.name: OPH_EXAM_DATA
merged.description: Stores ophthalmology exam information documented in the visit.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_THREADS
merged.description: This table contains information regarding a telephone encounter and any related messages.

merged.name: PAT_REVIEW_DATA
merged.description: Table contains patient entered clinical data review from Welcome Kiosk and MyChart.

merged.name: PAT_CR_TX_SINGLE
merged.description: This table contains single response information about the credit card transaction associated with an e-visit encounter that is stored in the patient record when the encounter is created.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_CALL_DATA
merged.description: This table contains miscellaneous data about clinical calls, such as the patient following the Care Advice.

merged.name: HOMUNCULUS_PAT_DATA
merged.description: Patient-specific rheumatology data, related to the homunculus joint exam.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_BILLING_ENC
merged.description: This table contains encounter-specific data related to Billing Encounters.

merged.name: PAT_ENC_CC_AUTO_CHG
merged.description: This table contains data related to a patient's encounter, specifically the patient giving consent for the charges linked to this encounter to be automatically paid by the patient's credit card.

merged.name: PAT_UTILIZATION_REVIEW
merged.description: This table contains information related to the patient utilization reviews entered during an admission.

merged.name: PATIENT_ENC_VIDEO_VISIT
merged.description: This table contains the video visit related data for a patient that is stored at the patient contact level.
